Round 1
[Patient] What foods can I eat to help with my heart failure?
[Educator] Try to limit salt and eat more fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins.

Round 2
[Patient] Can I still eat soul food like fried chicken and mac and cheese?
[Educator] It's best to limit fried foods and choose healthier cooking methods like baking or grilling.

Round 3
[Patient] What about sweets like cake and candy?
[Educator] Limit sugary treats and opt for fruits or yogurt for a sweet treat instead.

Round 4
[Patient] Will eating spicy foods like hot sauce or chili hurt my heart?
[Educator] Spicy foods in moderation are usually okay, but watch out for high sodium content.

Round 5
[Patient] Are there any specific foods that can help my heart get stronger?
[Educator] Foods like salmon, walnuts, and avocado are good for heart health. 

Round 6
[Patient] Can I still have a cup of coffee or tea in the morning?
[Educator] It's okay to have some caffeine but try to limit it and watch out for added sugars.

Round 7
[Patient] Are there any foods that I should absolutely avoid?
[Educator] Avoid foods high in saturated fats, trans fats, and excessive salt.

Round 8
[Patient] How important is it to drink water for my heart health?
[Educator] Staying hydrated with water is crucial for heart health and overall well-being.

Round 9
[Patient] What about alcohol, can I still have a drink occasionally?
[Educator] It's best to limit alcohol intake as it can worsen heart failure symptoms.

Round 10
[Patient] Can I still enjoy a bowl of popcorn while watching a movie?
[Educator] Popcorn can be a healthy snack if prepared without excess butter and salt.

Round 11
[Patient] How about fast food like burgers and fries, can I ever have that?
[Educator] Fast food should be limited due to high unhealthy fats, salt, and calories.

Round 12
[Patient] Can I have a small piece of dark chocolate for a treat?
[Educator] Dark chocolate in moderation can be a good choice for a sweet treat.

Round 13
[Patient] Is it okay to eat spicy foods like curry or jerk chicken?
[Educator] Spicy foods like curry or jerk chicken can be enjoyed in moderation.

Round 14
[Patient] Can I still eat traditional dishes like gumbo or jambalaya?
[Educator] Traditional dishes like gumbo or jambalaya can be made heart-healthy with lean meats and veggies.

